base URL (e.g. `https://example.com`)\n- `outputDir: string` -- output directory path\n- `contentDir: string` -- content directory path\n- `templateDir: string` -- template directory path\n\n**`ContentFile`** -- Represents a single content file to be processed:\n- `slug: string` -- URL-friendly identifier\n- `title: string` -- display title\n- `content: string` -- raw content (markdown or HTML)\n- `metadata: Record<string, unknown>` -- arbitrary key-value metadata\n- `date?: string` -- optional date string\n- `tags?: string[]` -- optional tag array\n- `template?: string` -- optional template name to use for rendering\n\n**`BuildContext`** -- Mutable state passed through the build pipeline:\n- `config: SiteConfig` -- the site config\n- `files: ContentFile[]` -- array of content files being processed\n- `output: Map<string, string>` -- output path to rendered content mapping\n- `assets: Map<string, Buffer>` -- output path to binary data mapping\n- `data: Map<string, unknown>` -- shared plugin data store (inter-plugin communication)\n\n**`PluginHooks`** -- The three lifecycle hooks a plugin can implement (all optional):\n- `beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs before content processing\n- `transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile` -- transforms a single file, returns modified file\n- `afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void` -- runs after all rendering\n\n**`Plugin`** -- The core plugin interface:\n- `name: string` -- unique plugin identifier\n- `version: string` -- semver version string\n- `dependencies: string[]` -- names of plugins this plugin depends on (used for topological sort)\n- `hooks: PluginHooks` -- the hook implementations\n\n**`Template`** -- A rendering template:\n- `name: string` -- template name (e.g. `'default'`, `'list'`)\n- `render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string` -- takes content + data, returns rendered HTML string\n\n-